  "prompt": "If you open a microwave oven before the beep will it release deadly microwave radiation?",
  "response": "No, opening a microwave oven before it beeps will not release deadly microwave radiation. Microwave ovens are designed with safety mechanisms to prevent this from happening. When you open the door, the microwave automatically stops generating microwaves, and the radiation ceases immediately. The interior of the microwave is only exposed to microwaves while the door is securely closed and the oven is in operation. Therefore, it is safe to open the microwave before the beep, as no harmful radiation will be released.",
